Text.Value: I reckon the murder we had's something to do with it too. Got punters all intrigued. On that morbid note - what can I get your fine self?
Tell you what - the murder upstairs has brought some punters, but it's also really spooked folk out of renting rooms.
You can have it for free if you stop talking. Bloody wizards.
I'll come back later.
Any chance of a discount?
Fair point. Here's the money. ([LOW_Elfsong_RentFullPrice_522a449e-a7f5-0d9b-c835-fc5a24d49d65])
The price just went up. Call it a shite-talk surcharge. ([LOW_Elfsong_RentOverpriced_c0839c4d-1481-70c1-e5c0-5a0aeaef4fb5])
Recite Elminster's journal entry about his free stay at the Elfsong Tavern.
Pull the other one - Guild folk don't chuck around Nine-Fingers' name like cheap dice.
I'll think about it.
You want [LOW_Elfsong_RentFullPrice_522a449e-a7f5-0d9b-c835-fc5a24d49d65] gold to sleep next to a murder scene? Really?
With all this talk of war - what else are folk to do but drink?
Insurance like that is mighty valuable at the moment. Sounds good to me.
Leave.
Point out the tavern's obvious dirt and grime - that should get you a discount.
Welcome back. What can I do you for?
Leave.
Look, mate, I don't want any trouble. Especially not from your lot.
At least, I hope.
Cut the price, and I'll spread word of this place for miles around.
Perhaps I could get a discount on the accommodation?
Going to make this place famous, I reckon. Victim is a bloody duke - Belynne Stelmane. Well, she was a duke. Now she's just bloody.
Well, the price ain't changed. Pockets deep enough? ([LOW_Elfsong_RentFullPrice_522a449e-a7f5-0d9b-c835-fc5a24d49d65])
*News of your good deeds has travelled fast. The merchant is all too happy to extend a certain generosity towards you, where the price of goods is concerned.*
Oi oi, pull up a seat - if you can find one spare, that is!
I reckon I'll be able to charge double for that room once the Constable's done with it. Murders and ghosts are always grand for business.
I'm still looking for somewhere to stay.
*Your notoriety precedes you. Prices have been moderated to reflect your less-than-welcome presence in the city.*
You're optimistic. What makes you so sure it'll all blow over?
NO! FOR MONEY.
Too rich for my boots.
Tell me more about the murder.
Business going well?
If I'm staying in this place, I'll make sure to protect it.
That'd be a great threat - if you weren't in the building too, genius.
I'm with the Guild. You'll be giving me the Nine-Finger discount.
Fill yer boots, mate!
Two little mistakes, pal. One - he actually stayed here in 1310 DR. Two - you're not Elminster. Bloody wizards.
Leave.
Oi, oi! I've got a good thing going here - don't need you casting nasty aspersions. You can have it free if you shut your maw.
If we get you staying up there, perhaps folk'll calm down and realise there's nowt to worry about.
Thinking's hard. Drinking's cheap.
Top floor's all yours. If it gets a bit too noisy at night, well, don't sleep above a pub.
If you happen across some coinage, you know where to find me.
Have you got anything to trade?
All right, ALL RIGHT! Calm down, you mad bastard.
Suit yourself.
I'm looking for a place to stay.
You can have the whole upstairs floor until this killer thing blows over. ([LOW_Elfsong_RentFullPrice_522a449e-a7f5-0d9b-c835-fc5a24d49d65])
Hand over the gold. ([LOW_Elfsong_RentFullPrice_522a449e-a7f5-0d9b-c835-fc5a24d49d65])
If I must. ([LOW_Elfsong_RentOverpriced_c0839c4d-1481-70c1-e5c0-5a0aeaef4fb5])
It's been slim pickings since the Absolute butchered that supply convoy - but have a look.
Commiserations. Perhaps a pint'll soothe your sorrows?
NO. FOR FREE.
It's called character. Anyone will tell you that.
(Keep your voice down about the bloody murder upstairs!) Ahem.
I could wave my hand and turn this place into rubble.
What good is your word? Invasion, murders, and lack of cash is what's putting folks off renting rooms.
Hah! Charity, in Baldur's Gate? Good one.
I'm afraid not.
More arses in chairs means more coin in my pouch. You've got yourself a deal.
You will protect it? Have you seen some of the big bastards around here?
The City always wins. There's always some hero that saves the day. It's the way things work.

Synopsis: The innkeeper at Elfsong Tavern sells a few supplies and allow players to rest at the tavern after paying a small quantity of gold.
